  "title": "Rotational dynamics - torque from forces on disk",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"Two figures are labeled 1 and 2. Figure 1 shows the top view of a disk with an arrow labeled F that is located at the top of the disk and points horizontally to the right, and another arrow labeled F that is located at the bottom of the disk and points horizontally to the left. Figure 2 shows the top view of a disk with an arrow labeled F that is located at the right edge of the disk and points horizontally to the right, and another arrow labeled F that is located at the bottom of the disk and points pointing horizontally to the left.\" src=\"/images/1eae6ec5643071529f0696aec5d726e9.svg\"></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The disk shown in the top-view figures is on a horizontal surface and is free to move with negligible friction. In both figures, two forces of magnitude <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F\"><math alttext=\"F\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>F</mi></math></span></span> are exerted on the disk at the locations and in the directions shown. Which of the following correctly indicates whether the net torque exerted on the disk about its center of mass is greater in Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> or Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, and provides a valid justification?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i1",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>, because both forces exert a clockwise torque.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>, because the net force on the disk is greater.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, because the line of action of one of the forces passes through the center of mass.</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, because the forces in Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> cancel each other out.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
      }
    ]
